Package projects.phonebook.hashes

Class LinearProbingHashTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • projects.phonebook.hashes.LinearProbingHashTable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HashTable
    public class LinearProbingHashTable
extends java.lang.Object
implements HashTable

    LinearProbingHashTable is an Openly Addressed HashTable implemented with Linear Probing as its collision resolution strategy: every key collision is resolved by moving one address over. It is the most famous collision resolution strategy, praised for its simplicity, theoretical properties and cache locality. It does, however, suffer from the " clustering " problem: collision resolutions tend to cluster collision chains locally, making it hard for new keys to be inserted without collisions. QuadraticProbingHashTable is a HashTable that tries to avoid this problem, albeit sacrificing cache locality.

    • Method Detail

      • put

        public void put​(java.lang.String key,
                java.lang.String value)
        Inserts the pair <key, value> into this. The container should not allow for null keys and values, and we will test if you are throwing a IllegalArgumentException from your code if this method is given null arguments! It is important that we establish that no null entries can exist in our database because the semantics of get(String) and remove(String) are that they return null if, and only if, their key parameter is null. This method is expected to run in amortized constant time. Instances of LinearProbingHashTable will follow the writeup's guidelines about how to internally resize the hash table when the capacity exceeds 50%

      • capacity

        public int capacity()
        Description copied from interface: HashTable
        Returns the capacity of this HashTable. In Separate Chaining, this is the total number of cells from which the lists begin. In Open Addressing methods, this method returns the size of the underlying array. As a consequence, in SeparateChainingHashTable, it's possible for HashTable.size() to return a value larger than this method. On the other hand, for Open Addressing methods like LinearProbingHashTable and QuadraticProbingHashTable, the value returned by this method is an upper bound on the value returned by HashTable.size().
        Specified by:
        capacity in interface HashTable
        Returns:
        the number of cells in the table.
